<div id="review_2478439096" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2478439096" />
    <a title="Victoria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22727329-victoria"><img alt="Victoria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467838647p2/22727329.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2478439096?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Victoria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Victoria" href="/user/show/22727329-victoria">Victoria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780143133124" href="/book/show/36588482-the-ruin">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2478439096" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14868427088848002289">There is solace in genre, knowing what kind of story to expect, and it seems that mysteries and thrillers are where I’m finding my comfort zone these days. Plot over prose, that’s my state of mind. So I’m digging back in the stacks, looking for those well-rated, but long languishing books and found this crime thriller gem.<br/><br/>It is right in the Tana French lane of Irish police procedurals, tightly written, masterfully plotted with a gothic feel to the past and a present day tension that grips and do</span>
  <span id="freeText14868427088848002289" style="display:none">There is solace in genre, knowing what kind of story to expect, and it seems that mysteries and thrillers are where I’m finding my comfort zone these days. Plot over prose, that’s my state of mind. So I’m digging back in the stacks, looking for those well-rated, but long languishing books and found this crime thriller gem.<br /><br />It is right in the Tana French lane of Irish police procedurals, tightly written, masterfully plotted with a gothic feel to the past and a present day tension that grips and doesn’t let go. There are two more in this series--The Scholar and The Good Turn--and it’s a good bet that I’ll read them before the year is through or I’ll owe you a Guinness.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14868427088848002289" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
